believe that people are most likely to be happy when they focus on their own personal goals. Once a person is focused on their own personal goals they can feel accomplished and productive which makes them feel happy. 
Everyone's personal goals are vastly different. To some, bringing happiness to others or improving humanity can be their personal goal. I do not believe that the happiness of others brings personal happiness because there are some people who are indifferent to other people's happiness.  Focusing on the happiness of others will also lead to a very difficult life because what brings happiness to one person can bring negative feelings towards another and if you are the one in the middle it is difficult to choose who's happiness is more important. Bringing happiness to others can also lead to people seeing you as a door mat because you are willing to sacrifice your own needs to make sure other people's needs and wants are being met. 
People must be careful to not make other's happiness their only personal goal though because that could also cause them to feel like their own happiness does not matter or is less important. It is important to find a balance of bringing happiness to others while also staying loyal to yourself and making sure that you are actually happy bringing happiness to others. 
Choosing personal goals to bring happiness can have it's downsides though because just as personal goals can be to bring other's happiness, they can also be selfish goals that can bring other's sadness or anger. For example, if someone's personal goal is to make as much money as possible they might go through means that are harmful to the environment or scam people.
